any ad champion can build lifesteal, but mages don't have that sort of sustain. as a result, any disparity in damage to resistance factors will cause a heavier upset, especially when it is directly countered by {{item:3147}} {{item:3036}} {{item:3033}} {{item:3142}} {{item:3071}} (oh look at this last one!){{item:3156}} 

meanwhile, in order to get offensive and armor defensive items for a mage you have two options on summoner's rift: {{item:3157}} (an active that isn't always useful, and{{item:3050}} (which is a support item. which is surprisingly little when you look at the life-steal items mentioned at the begining.

for pen items for mages, {{item:3001}} {{item:3151}} {{item:3020}} {{item:3135}} do an okay job, but it only really helps if you have sufficient base damages and reduces your effectiveness by trading off a needlessly large rod item, which is an okay trade off, but it doesn't happen for the ad counterparts which have significant ad save for maybe {{item:3153}}.

people just want one or two  medium armor items with either medium ap or moderate utility comparable to {{item:3025}} or {{item:3156}}
